Veeam Backup & Replication comes with the PowerShell extension
A Veeam Backup PowerShell module that is added to your machine when you either install Veeam Backup & Replication server or the Veeam Backup & Replication Console. 
The Veeam Backup PowerShell module allows you to do almost all operations that are available in the user interface. 
Keep in mind that actions performed with PowerShell have the same force as actions performed using Veeam Backup & Replication: 

Requirements
  1. To run Veeam PowerShell cmdlets, you must have Veeam Backup Administrator role. For more information, see Users and Roles.
  2. A machine that runs the PowerShell session must have Windows PowerShell version 5.1 installed.

Veeam Backup & Replication PowerShell Documentatrion: https://helpcenter.veeam.com/docs/backup/powershell/getting_started.html?ver=120
